n Hollander</b>), German (also <b>Holländer</b>), English, Swedish, and Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Holland (see   Holland   1)."]},{"name":"Holand","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Holland  .","Norwegian: habitational name from about twenty farmsteads so named, composed of Old Norse <i>hár</i> ‘high’ + <i>land</i> ‘land, field’, denoting a high-lying farm."]},{"name":"Aland","meanings":["Scandinavian (<b>Åland</b>): topographic name from the Åland Islands in the Gulf of Bothnia.","English: topographic name from Middle English <i>atte lande</i> (Old French <i>laund</i>) ‘dweller at the glade or pasture’, or sometimes perhaps, ‘dweller at the old cultivated land(s)’ from Old English <i>eald</i>, <i>ald</i> ‘old’ + <i>land</i> ‘land’."]},{"name":"Hollon","meanings":["English: altered form of   Holland  ."]}]},{"name":"Ieuan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Iohannes</i>.  See  <b>John</b>   ."],"variants":[{"name":"Iefan","meanings":["Later form of   Ieuan ."]},{"name":"Ifan","meanings":["From Latin <i>Iohannes</i>.  See  <b>John</b>   ."]},{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Ieuan Holland was born in Abergele, Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom as the son of Dafydd Holland and Dyddgu ferch Dafydd. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Mrs. Ieuan Holland."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1527–Male":"1527–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1505–Female":"1505–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1501–Male":"1501–Surnud","1470–Female":"1470–Surnud","1501":"1501","1470":"1470","1505":"1505","1527":"1527","of,Abergele,Denbighshire,Wales":"Abergele, Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1527–Male":"1527–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1505–Female":"1505–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1501–Male":"1501–Kuollut","1470–Female":"1470–Kuollut","1501":"1501",